13/03/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- EU Justice Commissioner Franco Frattini was due to arrive in Bucharest Monday (13 March) for talks with Romanian President Traian Basescu, Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu, Justice Minister Monica Macovei and Interior Minister Vasile Blaga. 
The focus is on key conditions for EU membership -- specifically, judicial reform and the fight against organised crime and corruption.
In other news, the Association for Transparency and Freedom of Expression presented the results of its recent survey Sunday. 
It found that 51.2 per cent of respondents in Romania believe political interference affects judicial action in cases of high-level corruption. 
(Rompres, Nine o'clock - 13/03/06)
